Hello =F0=9F=91=8B

It=E2=80=99s Pedro http://x.com/peduarte here =
with another monthly update! As always,
team picks at the bottom of the =
email.

By the way, you may notice this email looks a little different than=
 the previous
ones. That's because we've migrated to Resend and decided to =
simplify our
template. But I'll keep iterating and improving on it, so let =
me know what you
think!





YEARLY OFFSITE

The whole team got together in=
 Rovinj, Croatia, this year to celebrate our
yearly offsite. Aside from all=
 the travel disruptions, we had such a great time
together!

One of the things I love the most about our offsites is that it=E2=80=99s =
mainly
centered around people. Hanging out, doing fun activities, playing =
games, etc
and not full of work meetings for a whole week! We did hold a =
work-related
session in the morning, where Thomas and Petr shared an =
overview of how Raycast
is doing and what we=E2=80=99ve got planned for the=
 next year. And wow. I hope you=E2=80=99re
ready!

I selfishly took this =
opportunity to take a bunch of photos which I always enjoy
doing, you can check them out here
https://x.com/peduarte/status/1973389535=
657472149 to get a feel for the culture
at Raycast. Thanks to Sandy for =
organising this event. It gets harder each year
as the company grows.





A LITTLE GLASS

We=E2=80=99ve added a touch of Liquid Glass on both our =
macOS and iOS apps. Enjoy a
refreshed look, featuring rounder corners, =
updated app icons, and smooth
progressive blurs. Thomas shared some =
beautiful images of how it looks in Tahoe
https://x.=
com/thomaspaulmann/status/1967920772896395680 and iOS 26
https://x.com/thomaspaulmann/status/1968283679442239813. We also made a =
little
video where we talk about it a bit more. Check it out
https://x.com/peduarte/status/1967903168995754451 if you=E2=80=99re curious=
.





FUTURE FIFTY 2025

This year, we got selected to be part of the =
Future Fifty 2025 by TechNation.
Future Fifty is where late-stage UK tech =
levels up, with 30%+ of the country=E2=80=99s
unicorns coming through the =
program. We=E2=80=99re thrilled to join the lineup. Learn
more about it here https://technation.io/programmes/future-fifty/.





IN OTHER NEWS

=F0=9F=87=AF=F0=9F=87=B5 We=E2=80=99re hosting a hackathon =
https://raycast.connpass.com/event/369928/ and
community meetup =
https://raycast.connpass.com/event/370096/ in Tokyo at the end
of October

=E2=98=95 We got inspired by Cursor and Notion, and kicked off the =
Raycaf=C3=A9 trend. I
hosted the first one in Barcelona
https://x.com/peduarte/status/1972673141731164500, and Roy just did one in
Berlin https://x.com/RvRoo/status/1976607410795282686. The community is =
getting
involved and hosting them in various places around the world! =
Amazing to see.
Make sure to join one near you https://ray.so/events

=F0=9F=9B=A1=EF=B8=8F We=E2=80=99re enterprise ready with our SOC2 Type II =
certificate. Want to bring it
to your company? Let's talk =E2=86=92 =
enterprise@raycast.com enterprise@raycast.com

=F0=9F=90=A6 We crossed 80,=
000 Twitter followers https://x.com/raycast. I=E2=80=99m so impressed.
Thank you!

=F0=9F=A4=97 We=E2=80=99ve launched our Ambassador Program =
https://ray.so/ambassadors! Sign up so
you can also host a Raycaf=C3=A9!

=F0=9F=A7=98=E2=80=8D=E2=99=82=EF=B8=8F We're slowing down our release =
cycle for a little while. See Thomas'
announcement here https://x.=
com/thomaspaulmann/status/1976636662705705022.

=F0=9F=AA=9F Remember to =
sign up for the Windows raycast.com/windows waitlist.





TEAM PICKS

Time for everyone=E2=80=99s favorite part. Team picks!

=F0=9F=93=BD=EF=B8=8F=C2=A0Bruno watched the Palme D=E2=80=99Or winner It =
Was Just An Accident
https://boxd.it/TX2k and enjoyed how different it is.

=F0=9F=A4=BA=C2=A0Mathieu discovered what a tenon cutter
https://www.leevalley.com/en-us/shop/tools/hand-tools/dowel-and-tenon-cutte=
rs/42299-veritas-power-tenon-cutters
is and is looking forward to building =
some fences. TIL.

=E2=98=82=EF=B8=8F=C2=A0Beno=C3=AEt took his kids to see=
 My Neighbour Totoro https://totoroshow.com/ in
London. Oh I bet that was =
absolutely amazing.

=F0=9F=A5=B5=C2=A0Daniel finished reading Fever Pitch
https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4264.Fever_Pitch, recommended by his
football-obsessed friend.

=F0=9F=93=BA=C2=A0Adil watched MobLand =
https://www.imdb.com/fr/title/tt31510819/ and highly
recommends. Gonna check it out!

=F0=9F=9A=B4=C2=A0Johan got a new electric=
 bike
https://www.ecoride.com/en-se/?srsltid=3DAfmBOorFv4FfHGATWiYPBl6NKtJW=
L_4Clw-u8NfeAmJhsxsEZoClcnVS.
His new obsession!

=F0=9F=93=A6=C2=A0Hugo =
recommends makedo https://www.make.do/, which are basically cardboard
boxes for kids to create things with. They just built a spaceship with it. =
So
cool!

=F0=9F=94=A5=C2=A0Marcos bought a soldering iron
https://www.amazon.de/dp/B09B3XGWJG?ref=3Dppx_yo2ov_dt_b_fed_asin_title&th=
=3D1 and a
multi-meter
https://www.amazon.de/dp/B0011D6O0A?=
ref=3Dppx_yo2ov_dt_b_fed_asin_title to make
quick reparations at home.

=F0=9F=8E=A6=C2=A0John watched Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid
https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0064115/ in honour of the great Robert Redford=
.

=E2=9D=84=EF=B8=8F=C2=A0Samuel is ready for the Swedish winter with his =
new lightweight down jacket
https://haku-clothing.com/products/17066?=
srsltid=3DAfmBOorj9bz9zuoB5VqaObTSXaMf30BCTcBTXdcKoOPHE8LBUwdWXj_O.

=F0=9F=93=9A=C2=A0Alex S. has re-read Replay https://www.goodreads.=
com/book/show/341735.Replay.
A science fiction, where the main character =
lives his life from 18 to 43 over
and over again.

=F0=9F=92=A1=C2=A0Thomas=
 got this really beautiful lamp
https://www.madeindesign.co.=
uk/prod-lop-small-rectangle-table-lamp-plastic-material-transparent-archipr=
oducts-design-award-winner-bang-refm115920701.html.
Next time we make a video with him, you=E2=80=99ll see it in his background=
!

=F0=9F=8E=9F=EF=B8=8F=C2=A0Petr managed to grab Radiohead tickets for =
their London concert!

=F0=9F=A7=B6 As usual Steph got a bunch of wool. 9.=
5kg this time!

=F0=9F=93=B8=C2=A0And I got this tiny Godox IM20 =
https://amzn.eu/d/apXR6zc flash, USB
chargeable. Love it.




That's it for this month. For all changes, check out our=C2=A0changelog
https://www.raycast.com/changelog.

See you next month!

